author: Nexcell Pride
text:
Yes... Another great stream today. :_るんるん:
Today's chapter, how to build an Self-cultivatitive machine?

Wow... Rushia using materials for useful machines and inventions, meanwhile the rest (Not all) uses materials for making traps, bombs and giant mechas (Like Pekodam and Shubangelion)

Many materials... First of all, the functional pieces and the first tests.
Later of that, the aesthetical pieces for external view.

Also strange materials like blue flames were present.

3:00:26 Freeze... But... 

3:01:07 That sound, Minecraft paused and Rushia-daitenshi's Live2D stopped... Something went wrong. Fortunately it was a connection issue, but solved.

3:23:54 Oh... And a bad trader and his llamas...
Later of trader killed, llamas kept attacking, until one of them was captured, but with the bad luck it was over flames and got sacrified.
(Sacrifice and with blue flames... It seems a good place for Sakura Miko)

Later, finally done... Also the "Free take" Sign (Rushia has a good english knowledge) :_ちょうちょ:

And the Supaachaato Orei Time was short, due to no short Zatsudan part available, but took the time already. :_きゅん: :_ハート:

author: Redan Kenneth Uy
text:
Youtubeではコメントを長くしたり編集したりすると非表示になってしまうので、返信にタイムスタンプを入れることにしました。タイムスタンプもYoutubeが非表示にならないように分割します。 Since Youtube hides my comment if I made it long or edit, I decide to put the timestamps in the reply. I will divide the timestamps so that Youtube won't hide them too.

もしタイムスタンプが完全でない場合は、私がまだ作業中であるか、または表示されるように十分に短くしようとしていることを意味します。気長にお待ちください。ご迷惑をおかけして申し訳ありません。 If the timestamps is not complete, it means I am still working on them or I am trying to shorten them enough to appear. Please be patient. Sorry for the inconvenience.
